# External-Call Retry Policy

> **Locked:** SPEC 19 Phase F (S.135, 2026-05-09). Audited every external call site in t2000-engine + audric/web. Documents what's already shipped + what we deliberately don't retry.

## D-5 contract (the lock)

| Class | Attempts | Retry on | NEVER retry on | Why asymmetric |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Reads** (BV, Anthropic, Sui RPC queries, SuiNS) | **3** baseline (extends to 5 for shared-object burst contention) | 5xx, 429, network err (ECONNRESET/ETIMEDOUT/EPIPE/HeadersTimeout), AbortError from upstream timeout | 4xx other than 429 (client error — won't change), AbortError from caller (caller cancelled — respect) | Reads are idempotent. Re-trying a successful-on-retry read costs only latency, not money or state. |
| **Writes** (Enoki sponsor, Enoki execute, Sui submit) | **1** | (none — surface error to user) | (everything) | Re-submitting a write risks double-spend. Idempotency keys could enable safe retries; not worth the complexity at current scale. |
| **Wait/poll** (Sui `waitForTransaction`) | **1** outer retry; SDK handles internal RPC polling | (delegated to SDK) | (delegated to SDK) | The poll IS the retry — wrapping it in another retry layer would amplify backoff. |

**Anything that doesn't fit one of these three classes** → no retry by default; document the reason if added later.

